{"id":789517537,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"9 months, 4 weeks","timestamp":1662110502,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"6 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/789517537/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Recover Binary Search Tree","memory":"47.2 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * public class TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode left;\n *     TreeNode right;\n *     TreeNode() {}\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\n *         this.val = val;\n *         this.left = left;\n *         this.right = right;\n *     }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    public void recoverTree(TreeNode root) {\n        PriorityQueue<Integer> pq= new PriorityQueue<>();\n        \n        Inorder(root,pq);\n        arrange(root,pq);\n        \n    }\n    public void Inorder(TreeNode root,PriorityQueue<Integer> pq){\n        if(root==null){\n            return;\n}\n        Inorder(root.left,pq);\n        pq.add(root.val);\n        Inorder(root.right,pq);\n    }\n    public void arrange(TreeNode root,PriorityQueue<Integer> pq){\n        if(root==null){\n            return;\n        }\n        arrange(root.left,pq);\n        int curr=pq.poll();\n        if(curr!=root.val){\n            root.val=curr;\n        }\n        arrange(root.right,pq);\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"recover-binary-search-tree","has_notes":false}
